 class=3D"google_cta_icon-pdHW3"></span></div><h1 data-testid=3D"article-ti=
tle" class=3D"article_hed-lWOBk"><p>How to Identify a Prime Number without =
a Computer</p></h1><div class=3D"article_dek-vct0y"><p>For years, a French =
mathematician searched for a proof that a gigantic number is prime. His met=
hod is still used 150 years later</p></div><p class=3D"article_authors-ZdsD=
4">By <a class=3D"article_authors__link--hwBj" href=3D"https://www.scientif=
icamerican.com/author/manon-bischoff/">Manon Bischoff</a> <span class=3D"ar=
ticle_editors__links-aMTdN">edited by <a class=3D"article_authors__link--hw=
Bj" href=3D"https://www.scientificamerican.com/author/daisy-yuhas/">Daisy Y=
uhas</a></span></p><figure class=3D"lead_image-Hfr4j"><img src=3D"https://s=
tatic.scientificamerican.com/dam/m/56087a8ff6d6adcc/original/GettyImages-66=
9891874-prime-numbers.jpeg?m=3D1762893627.436&amp;w=3D600" alt=3D"abstract =
